34:37.876 --> 34:44.115 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
How does that fit into what you
see as maybe
this developing, evolving vision
and mission

34:44.149 --> 34:45.984 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of the Episcopal Church?

34:46.017 --> 34:48.586 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MDNM /THE MOST REVEREND MICHAEL
CURRY: Scholars,
sometimes, when they look at the
origins of

34:48.620 --> 34:53.191 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Christianity, they often use the
phrase the
Jesus movement as a way of
describing what

34:53.224 --> 34:59.197 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Jesus of Nazareth actually was
doing in the
earliest days in Palestine, that
the Jesus

34:59.230 --> 35:03.835 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
movement in the first and second
and third
centuries was a movement of
people who gathered

35:03.868 --> 35:06.705 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
around the teachings of Jesus of
Nazareth.

35:06.738 --> 35:10.942 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And their gathering around and
committing
themselves to that way of life
that Jesus

35:10.976 --> 35:16.781 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
