the artillery
range.

41:21.312 --> 41:25.950 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Why? Well, it turns out that
bombs actually
benefit this butterfly.

41:25.983 --> 41:28.186 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAN GROSBOLL, Insect Biologist,
Joint Base
Lewis-McChord: If you're an
individual butterfly

41:28.219 --> 41:35.193 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
