the training
ignites fires across the
landscape, and improves

41:42.667 --> 41:47.171 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
the habitat across the
landscape, overall,
it is likely good for the
butterfly population.

41:47.205 --> 41:53.444 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CAT WISE: Dan Grosboll is an
insect biologist
at the base who has to be very,
very careful

41:53.478 --> 41:56.581 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
when he's out looking for
butterflies amid
artillery shells.

41:56.614 --> 42:00.251 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAN GROSBOLL: They have a very
brief adult
life span. And the rest of the
life span,

42:00.284 --> 42:02.720 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
